headline: Is Amazon Still a Millionaire-Maker Stock?
summary: With shares up by over 240,000% since hitting public markets in 1997, Amazon (NASDAQ: AMZN) is a quintessential example of this trend.  Under the leadership of CEO Andy Jassy, who took the helm from Jeff Bezos in 2021, Amazon has shifted its strategy from growth at all costs to prioritizing profitability.  The company has slashed thousands of white-collar positions, streamlined its fulfillment network, and trimmed less-profitable business ventures.
